<p>Tropical Storm Melissa strengthened and is forecast to become a hurricane as it moved toward the northern Caribbean, threatening Jamaica, Haiti and the Dominican Republic with heavy rain, life-threatening flooding and landslides . The storm has already been linked to at least four deaths — three in Haiti and one in the Dominican Republic — as emergency services and communities brace for more severe weather . Forecasters warned the system could intensify further in the coming days, raising the risk of catastrophic flash flooding and dangerous conditions along coastal and mountainous areas .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/_eINBdVDdYO4MKZpTkmf_D_KHFoXziqUyzcFie_TKK8aO2_cgSi-mHh3Po5KMzxF3G-AfhvC4_U3Fm1ZeCU2nZLFBFBx2MuWOCg5c1wlg1l2475nkgJsesmgkGHBjD5ATQvOE8OEFp_BIAiNonFWTIvDLNoteuqANQz5O2YZPg' alt='Satellite view of Tropical Storm Melissa as it approaches the northern Caribbean' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Major hurricane risk: Meteorologists warned Melissa could strengthen into a major hurricane (Category 3 or higher), which would sharply increase the chance of catastrophic flash flooding and landslides in vulnerable terrain .</li><li>Fatalities breakdown: Reporting indicates at least three people died in Haiti and one person died in the Dominican Republic, bringing the confirmed death toll to at least four so far .</li><li>Prolonged impacts: Jamaican officials prepared for extended hazardous conditions, with forecasts warning of sustained hurricane-force weather for multiple days and heavy rainfall that could overwhelm drainage systems and roads .</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Forecasters: Meteorological services and storm trackers warned Melissa could intensify to hurricane strength and produce life‑threatening rainfall and flooding over the northern Caribbean in the coming days. (<a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/tropical-storm-melissa-poised-become-hurricane-drop-torrential-126856057'>ABC News</a>)</li><li>Local authorities (Jamaica, Haiti, Dominican Republic): Governments and emergency services urged residents to prepare and take warnings seriously as the storm approaches, with communities told to expect dangerous flooding and possible landslides. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/25/tropical-storm-melissa-soon-a-hurricane-brings-death-floods-to-caribbean'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/25/tropical-storm-melissa-soon-a-hurricane-brings-death-floods-to-caribbean'>Tropical Storm Melissa, soon a hurricane, brings death, floods to Caribbean</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/deadly-tropical-storm-melissa-pummels-caribbean/a-74493409'>Deadly Tropical Storm Melissa pummels Caribbean</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/tropical-storm-melissa-poised-become-hurricane-drop-torrential-126856057'>Tropical Storm Melissa poised to become a hurricane and drop torrential rain on Caribbean</a> - abcnews.go.com</li><li><a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/melissa-maps-forecast-atlantic-ocean/'>Melissa becoming major threat to Jamaica, Haiti, Dominican Republic</a> - cbsnews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/live/2025/10/23/weather/tropical-storm-melissa-hurricane'>At least four people are killed in Haiti and the Dominican Republic by Tropical Storm Melissa.(The New York Times)</a> - nytimes.com</li></ul>